                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d9">
                        <locus target="#72r" facs="074">Fol. 72r</locus>
                        <desc>Two flying <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1082Angel">Angel</ref> each with a <term key="sword" ana="#sword"/>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d10">
                        <locus target="#140r" facs="142">Fol. 140r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1099StMary">St Mary</ref> raises the painter who fell from a scaffolding  with caption <q><foreign xml:lang="am">ሠዓሊው፡ ከመሰላስ፡ በወደቀ፡ ጊዜ፡ ማርያም፡ አነሣችው።</foreign></q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>

                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d11">
                        <locus from="140v" to="141r" facs="143">Fols 140v–141r</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1016Flight">Flight into Egypt</ref>. On <locus target="#140v" facs="143">fol. 140v</locus> the caption reads <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያምና፡ ዮሴፍ፡</foreign></q>
                        On <locus target="#141r" facs="143">fol. 141r</locus> the caption reads <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርታና፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ሰሎሜ፡</foreign></q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d12">
                        <locus target="#141v" facs="144">Fol. 141v</locus>
                        <desc>A priest blessing people with his hand <term key="cross" ana="#cross"/>
                           <ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> with caption <q><foreign xml:lang="gez">መስቀል፡ አሳለሙ፡</foreign></q>
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d13">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#107r #139v" facs="109 142">fols. 107r, 139v</locus> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using multiple colors);
                      <locus target="#1r #6v #51r" facs="003 009 053">1r, 6v, 51r</locus> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using black and red);
                      <locus target="#6r" facs="008">6r</locus> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> using red);
                      <locus target="#6r #17v #19r #19v #28r #28v #36r #125v #134v #135v" facs="008 020 021 022 030 031 038 0128 137 138">6r, 17v, 19r, 19v, 28r, 28v, 36r, 125v, 134v, 135v, </locus> (dotted line using alternating black and red);
                      <locus target="#82v" facs="085">82v, </locus> (dotted line using alternating black and red with blue marks added);
                      <locus target="#21v #96r" facs="024 098">21v, 96r, </locus> (dotted line using black);
                      <locus target="#67v #93r #101v #105v #119r" facs="070 095 104 108 121">67v, 93r, 101v, 105v, 119r</locus> (dotted line using red)
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc>Overlooked words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#138v" facs="141">fol. 138v</locus>)</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                          The scribe regularly has to complete a line of text on another line. Much of the problem is addressed through the selection of an
                          appropriate aspect ratio for the codex combined with an appropriate script size. But, where the line of text is still too long, the scribe
                          completes the line of text above the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#1v #2v #3r #4v" facs="004 005 007">folss. 1v, 2v, 3r, 4v, </locus>, etc.). This scribe will also reduce the font size at the end of
                          lines to avoid having to go onto the next line (e.g., <locus target="#55v #57v" facs="058 060">55v, 57v</locus>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
